Apology and compliance history
==============================

Apology to Michail Vasileiadis and the Hacker Bob contributors
--------------------------------------------------------------

Mantis incorporates substantial verbatim ports of Apache-2.0-licensed
prompt and agent files from Hacker Bob
(https://github.com/vmihalis/hacker-bob, Copyright 2026 Michail
Vasileiadis). For an interval prior to 2026-05-25, this repository
distributed those ported files without satisfying several of the
formal requirements of Apache License 2.0 §4. Specifically, the
project:

  - declared `Apache-2.0 OR MIT` in `README.md` and `Cargo.toml` but
    did NOT include the actual `LICENSE-APACHE` / `LICENSE-MIT` text
    files on disk, in violation of §4(a);
  - referenced Hacker Bob in its own NOTICE and `CONTRAST.md` but did
    NOT reproduce the upstream Hacker Bob NOTICE text verbatim, in
    violation of §4(d);
  - did NOT carry per-file "prominent notices stating that You changed
    the files" on the ported files under
    `plugin/claude-code/agents/` and `prompts/roles/`, in violation
    of §4(b).

We apologize to Michail Vasileiadis and the Hacker Bob project for
distributing derivative work with these §4 mechanics incomplete. The
attribution was real — the upstream credit, the per-file ports
inventory in `CONTRAST.md`, and the architectural acknowledgement in
this NOTICE all predated the cure — but real attribution is not a
substitute for the §4 formalities, and we should have included the
license texts, propagated the upstream NOTICE, and added per-file
change headers from the first publication. We did not, and that was a
license violation. The cure does not erase the gap; it documents it.

Cure
----

Fully remediated on 2026-05-25 on `main`:

  53d9b4f  Merge #18 — add LICENSE-APACHE + LICENSE-MIT on disk (§4(a)),
           reproduce the upstream Hacker Bob NOTICE verbatim under a
           clearly-labeled "Upstream NOTICE" section (§4(d)), and
           correct prior NOTICE wording that downplayed the verbatim
           port — agent and role prompts ARE verbatim ports with
           tool-name renames, as already documented in CONTRAST.md.
  c59fdba  Merge #19 — add §4(b) "prominent notice of changes"
           headers to 35 ported files in `plugin/claude-code/agents/`
           and `prompts/roles/`, naming the upstream URL, copyright
           holder, license, and the concrete renames applied
           (`bounty_*` → `mantis_*`, session paths, completion markers).
  a83489e  Merge #20 — record this Compliance history in NOTICE so the
           gap and cure are documented in the repository itself, not
           only in PR descriptions.

A public paper trail has also been filed as an issue on the upstream
repository (https://github.com/vmihalis/hacker-bob) so the maintainer
has direct notice.

No source code, no attribution, and no derivation lineage was
concealed during the gap window — `CONTRAST.md` openly documented the
verbatim port from the start, and Hacker Bob has been named in this
NOTICE since the first commit. The violation was strictly the missing
§4 mechanics. The cure brings the project into full §4 compliance.
Grateful acknowledgement to Michail Vasileiadis and the Hacker Bob
contributors for the upstream work that made Mantis possible.

